The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable Internet links.  Rooney Request  Wayne Rooney will submit a written request to leave
Manchester United this week, putting more pressure on the team
to trade him to Chelsea,  the Daily Express  reported.  Chelsea will improve its offer for the England striker to
30 million pounds ($46 million), according to the Express.  Palace Coup  Crystal Palace could sign Aston Villaâ€™s England striker
Darren Bent,  the Daily Mirror  reported.  The 29-year-old is interested in joining the Premier League
newcomer, which is based near where he was born in south  London ,
the Mirror said.  Bale Exchange  Tottenham wants 20-year-old striker Alvaro Morata in
exchange as well as a fee of 87 million pounds to trade Gareth Bale to Real Madrid,  the Independent  reported.  Spurs Chairman Daniel Levy and Real Madrid President
Florentino Perez are scheduled to meet in  Florida  this week,
according to the Independent.  England Youth  Liverpool and Arsenal are vying to sign England youth-team
midfielder Dele Alli from MK Dons, the  Daily Mirror  reported.  The 6-foot-2 Alli could be sold to one of the Premier
League teams and loaned back to MK Dons, the Mirror said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
